   {:e #blake3 "e75198ac1a00ff8edb3b8c867e7c95eb84228de4471e15addb8a814955d58375" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The seed assembles context using score = 0.5*relevance + 0.3*significance + 0.2*recency. This ignores the most powerful epistemic signal: independent corroboration. Two agents independently finding the same bug is epistemically stronger than one agent finding it at high confidence. The seed also has no section for surfacing convergent findings or cross-agent agreements. RATIONALE: This is the INTEGRATION task — it wires C9-P1 (agreement detection) and C9-P2 (link extraction) into the seed assembly pipeline. But it is designed as a MINIMAL, REVERSIBLE integration, not a monolithic rewrite. If agreement data is unavailable (C9-P1 not run, or no multi-agent session), the seed falls back to the existing formula with zero degradation. APPROACH — THREE CHANGES: CHANGE 1: Add optional corroboration parameter to score_entity(). New signature adds corroboration_map: &BTreeMap<EntityId, f64>. New formula: 0.4*relevance + 0.25*significance + 0.15*recency + 0.2*corroboration. When corroboration_map is empty (no multi-agent data), the 0.2 weight redistributes: 0.5*relevance + 0.3*significance + 0.2*recency (IDENTICAL to current behavior). This means the change is backward-compatible by construction. CHANGE 2: In assemble(), conditionally compute agreement clusters. If the store has observations from 2+ distinct agents (cheap check: scan a few :tx/agent values), call find_agreement_clusters() from C9-P1. Build corroboration_map mapping observation EntityIds to their cluster's agreement_score. Pass to score_entity(). If single-agent store, pass empty map (fallback to original formula). CHANGE 3: Add convergent findings subsection to build_orientation(). After session accomplishments, if agreement_clusters is non-empty, add: 'Convergent findings (N agents agree):' followed by top 5 clusters ranked by agreement_score, each with: topic summary, agent count, confidence range, dependency chain (from C9-P2 links via VAET traversal). This goes in Orientation (structural context), which is compressed AFTER State entries — convergent findings survive longer under budget pressure than individual entity entries. ALGEBRAIC PROPERTIES: (1) Backward-compatible: empty corroboration map produces identical output to current seed. (2) Monotonic improvement: adding a corroborating agent can only increase an observation's score (agreement_score is monotonically non-decreasing). (3) Budget-safe: convergent findings are capped at 5 entries (~100 tokens), well within Orientation budget allocation. ACCEPTANCE: (A) With single-agent store, seed output is byte-identical to current implementation. (B) With 3-agent store where 2 agents agree on finding X, finding X appears in Convergent findings section. (C) Convergent findings survive budget compression when State entries are dropped. (D) score_entity proptest: for any entity, score with empty corroboration map == score with current formula within epsilon. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs. EFFORT: 4h." :op :assert}
